Cleaning the Data

In the above Data, the players can be intially segragated based on the following parameter.

1.Capped - Batters, Bowlers, Allrounders, Wicket keepers

2.Uncapped - Batters, Bowlers, Allrounders, Wicket keepers.

The uncapped players are playing IPL for the first time, or relevant data isn't available therefore we have used their domestic T20 performance and T20 international performance.

In [12]:
#segragating Data - Capped Batters
#We have kept the batting performance to restrict the analysis for the specific tendencies.
batters = data.loc[(data["Player_Type"] == "Batter")]

batters_new = batters.loc[(batters["Capped"] == 1)]

Capped_Batters = batters_new[['Player Name', 
                              'Team', 
                              'Nationality', 
                              'Matches_Played', 
                              'Runs', 
                              'Average', 
                              'Strike_Rate']]

Forming Our Best 11 for the Campaign based on the above analysis

1.We will consider the number of players from each category that the t20 world cup winning and winning and last 
  year's IPL winning team played in their matches.

2.The Austarlian squad consisted of -3 Batters, 3 Allrounders, 4 Bowlers with 1 spin option and 1 wicketkeeper

3.The chennai squad consisted of -4 Batters, 3 Allrounders, 3 Bowlers and 1 Wicketkeeper.

4.For our final analysis we will consider the ratio of the players in the best 11 as follows:

   1. 3 Batters
   2. 3 Allrounders
   3. 4 Bowlers with 2 spin options
   4. 1 Wicket Keeper
